1. Open Terminal (Linux/Mac) or Git Bash (Windows)
2. Navigate to the location where you want to create the repository
3. Create a new folder named as your enrollment number  Replace ENROLLMENT_NO with your actual number.
4. Initialize it as a Git repository
5. Create two folders: assignment1 and assignment2 bash Copy Edit
6. Add the folders to Git staging area
7. Commit the changes
8. (Optional) Push to GitHub
  If you want to upload this to GitHub:
  Create a repository on GitHub with the same name (ENROLLMENT_NO)
  then connect it using:
  
